{
  "abstract": "Mineralizing activities cf different inoculated microorganisms during degradation of straw\r\nwere studied. The inoculated microorganisms showed an increased release of ammonical and\r\nnitrate nitrogen during degradation. Inoculation has proved its special role in mineralization\r\nof phosphorus. Penicilliltm sp. was found to be most active in releasing available phosphorus.\r\nThe amount of potash declined as the degradation progressed.\r\n",
